metadata.name: Splinter #235
metadata.description:
This release marks my first anniversary on the fx(hash) platform! I want to extend a huge thank you to everyone for a fantastic year, and I'm looking forward to many more in the generative-art world!

The basic algorithm is an evolution of the one I used in my first release, Raked Strokes. Instead of mimicking a brush with parallel segments, I'm using perpendicular line segments to define the overall abstract shape and then drawing each line in a simulated media. This approach blends my first attempts at natural media with everything I've learned in the past year.

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.
Press 's' to save a screenshot. The image size is 2357x3000px
Press 'p' to pause/resume during drawing.

Features
- Base path shape: line, circle, diamond, or rectangle
- Elements defining the spacing and orientation of the line segments
- The base path painted in the background
- Monochrome, dark background, and selection of palettes
- Ink pen styling: thickness, quality, and background blocking
- Paint styling: color distribution, quality
- Shapes: triangle, polygons, criteria for insertion
- Shapes overdrawing: outlines or perpendicular segments

metadata.name: Protein Pelt #419
metadata.description:
An incorrectly placed decimal point led to this pattern. A good friend told me it reminded them of protein structures, I found them to look like animal pelts strewn about.

Each "protein" is made up of 100 pelts, random walking around the canvas from the center. Each "pelt" is made of 5 colors sampled from an array of 84 colors.

Press 's' when in live view to save the image.

metadata.name: Meander River Plot v2 #201
metadata.description: A calmer version of the meander algorithm. Just the loops of the line vectors with no influence from a noise field. I love watching these loop and swirl as I'm developing the piece - it's fun and relaxing.

metadata.name: Plottable Mandelglitch #88
metadata.description:
This is a plottable re-exploration of Mandelglitch, a shader I created in 2020. It combines various mandelbrot fractal distortions, noise and domain warping. 21 different inks palette and 5 different paper are possible.

This generator uses fx(params) which allows the minter to partially finetune the art, making this a co-creation. I have chosen to allow to be able to configure all chaotic behaviors of these piece: the layers, density and distortion factors – however the paper/ink palette remain chosen by RNG (with the possibility to limit the colors from that palette). Take the time to play with the parameters, less can be better sometimes!

request a physical plot from @greweb at https://greweb.me/plots/nft – The NFT is ultimately the recipe to a physically plottable art piece, it exports a SVG that you can plot with pens – plotter artists are free to use their own materials and ship to collectors as long as the NFT is owned at the time of the request. Simply drag&drop (or right-click-save) in a folder to get the .SVG.

metadata.name: Canevach #142
metadata.description:
Canevach started as a code golfing experiment, 280 characters of HTML, CSS and JavaScript producing pixelated patterns when copy-pasted in the address bar of a web browser.

The code has been adapted for the sake of entropy control and readability, but I tried to keep it as lean as possible to honour the code golfing spirit that initiated the project.

The artwork is generated by manipulating pixels directly through the Canvas API.

Colours are uniformly selected in RGB space, without any colour theory considerations. The only exception is for black, which is made more prominent by the way the algorithm is initiated.

Features
• Canvas size: 8x8 | 16x16 | 32x32 | 64x64 | 128x128
• Number of colours: 1 to 5
